{"key":"processedPost-12267070","value":{"id":12267070,"first":12266508,"last":12267959,"when":1269496562,"utime":"03/25/10 08:56 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>master_silly said:</b><br />so lets say i have oh idk 10 56 quart mono tubs max in a standard closet.. id opt to have a lot more cfl light then ehhh?<br /></blockquote><br /><br />First of all, that's too many tubs for a closet.&nbsp; The air will become saturated with CO2 and performance will be poor at best.&nbsp; Mushrooms require fresh air to pin properly and lots of it, so keep your tubs in an open room, and if you have a lot of them, keep the window open for constant fresh air into the room.<br /><br />For large amounts of tubs, you're better off with fluorescent tubes, which will spread the light over a larger area.&nbsp; I have a few 4 tube, 48\" fixtures with cords attached so I can move them around as needed.&nbsp; As said, get 6500 Kelvin color temperature tubes, not UV light which could destroy mycelium tissue and/or give you cancer.<br />RR","title":"Re: UV light for fruiting?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}